@node "E-Security ??" "E-Security ??"

                            @{fg shine}S e c u r i t y   ? ?@{fg text}


@{b}Security BM@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-100@{fg text}
   Security Level for Bulletins Menu

@{b}Security FS@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-100@{fg text}
   Security Level for File System

@{b}Security MB@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-100@{fg text}
   Security Level for Message Board

@{b}Security PM@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-100@{fg text}
   Security Level for Private Mail

@{b}Security SM@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-100@{fg text}
   Security Level for Setup Menu

@{b}Security UM@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-100@{fg text}
   Security Level for User Menu

See also @{"¦Cycle Gadget 1" link "E-¦Cycle Gadget 1" 0}
@endnode

@node "E-Total ??" "E-Total ??"

                               @{fg shine}T o t a l   ? ?@{fg text}


@{b}Total RM`s@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-65535@{fg text}
   Displays the number of Read Message

@{b}Total WM`s@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-65535@{fg text}
   Displays the number of Write Message

@{b}Total RP`s@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-65535@{fg text}
   Displays the number of Read Private Mail

@{b}Total WP`s@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-65535@{fg text}
   Displays the number of Write Private Mail
@endnode

@node "E-Average CPS" "E-Average CPS"

                            @{fg shine}A v e r a g e   C P S@{fg text}


@{b}Average CPS@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-65535@{fg text}
   Displays the average CPS rate of the last download
@endnode

@node "E-Nr of Lines" "E-Nr of Lines"

                            @{fg shine}N r   o f   L i n e s@{fg text}


@{b}Nr of Lines@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-255@{fg text}
   Displays the number of lines per page
@endnode

@node "E-Emulation" "E-Emulation"

                              @{fg shine}E m u l a t i o n@{fg text}


@{b}Emulation@{ub} : @{fg fill}Undefined|TTY|TTY+CLS|ANSI|ANSI+CLS@{fg text}
   Setting of the emulation
   @{fg fill}TTY@{fg text}      = 2 colors without control characters
   @{fg fill}TTY+CLS@{fg text}  = 2 colors with clear screen
   @{fg fill}ANSI@{fg text}     = 8 colors without control characters
   @{fg fill}ANSI+CLS@{fg text} = 8 colors with clear screen
@endnode

@node "E-Help Text" "E-Help Text"

                              @{fg shine}H e l p   T e x t@{fg text}


@{b}Help Text@{ub} : @{fg fill}Undefined|OFF|Medium|ON@{fg text}
   Setting of the Help Text
   @{fg fill}OFF@{fg text}    = No display of the Help Text
   @{fg fill}Medium@{fg text} = Display in the short form (2 characters) in 1 line
   @{fg fill}ON@{fg text}     = Display of the complete Help Text
   NOTE: The complete Help Text can be displayed with ?? or Enter
         independent of the setting.
@endnode

@node "E-List Form" "E-List Form"

                              @{fg shine}L i s t   F o r m@{fg text}


@{b}List Form@{ub} : @{fg fill}Undefined|US-2LA-AL|US-1LC-AL|US-1LB-AL|@{fg text}
                      @{fg fill}US-2LA-SI|US-1LC-SI|US-1LB-SI|@{fg text}
                      @{fg fill}SN-2LA-AL|SN-1LC-AL|SN-1LB-AL|@{fg text}
                      @{fg fill}SN-2LA-SI|SN-1LC-SI|SN-1LB-SI|@{fg text}
                      @{fg fill}SD-2LA-AL|SD-1LC-AL|SD-1LB-AL|@{fg text}
                      @{fg fill}SD-2LA-SI|SD-1LC-SI|SD-1LB-SI@{fg text}
   Setting of the List Form. By combination of the following options you
   will get 18 different settings.
   @{fg fill}US@{fg text}  = unsorted
   @{fg fill}SN@{fg text}  = sorted by name
   @{fg fill}SD@{fg text}  = sorted by date
   @{fg fill}2LA@{fg text} = 2 lines all    -> 2 lines with all information
   @{fg fill}1LC@{fg text} = 1 line comment -> 1 line with comment
   @{fg fill}1LB@{fg text} = 1 line bytes   -> 1 line with bytes, date and time
   @{fg fill}AL@{fg text}  = all            -> all information
   @{fg fill}SI@{fg text}  = since          -> with request for input of a date
@endnode

@node "E-Ratio" "E-Ratio"

                                  @{fg shine}R a t i o@{fg text}


@{b}Ratio@{ub} : @{fg fill}Undefined|OFF|Quantity|Bytes|Both@{fg text}
   Setting of the UL/DL ratio.
   @{fg fill}OFF@{fg text}      = no limitation
   @{fg fill}Quantity@{fg text} = The number of the downloads is equivalent to the ratio of
              UL/DL.
              e.g. UL Ratio = 1 and DL Ratio = 5 means that the user can
              make 5 downloads for each upload independent of the size of
              the file.
   @{fg fill}Bytes@{fg text}    = The size of the download files is equivalent to the ratio of
              UL/DL.
              e.g. UL ratio = 1 and DL ratio = 5 means that the user can
              download 5 bytes for every uploaded byte no matter in how
              many files.
   @{fg fill}Both@{fg text}     = That is the combination of Quantity and Bytes. Downloads are
              only possible if both requirements are true.

See also @{"¦Cycle Gadget 1" link "E-¦Cycle Gadget 1" 0}
@endnode

@node "E-UL Protocol" "E-UL Protocol"

                            @{fg shine}U L   P r o t o c o l@{fg text}


@{b}UL Protocol@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-99@{fg text}
   Display of the Upload Protocol Number. See bbs.config to get more
   information or via SysOp Logon in the Setup Menu with the command
   Change Transfer. Here are all available protocols listed.
@endnode

@node "E-DL Protocol" "E-DL Protocol"

                            @{fg shine}D L   P r o t o c o l@{fg text}


@{b}DL Protocol@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-99@{fg text}
   Display of the Download Protocol Number. See bbs.config to get more
   information or via SysOp Logon in the Setup Menu with the command
   Change Transfer. Here are all available protocols listed.
@endnode

@node "E-UL Ratio" "E-UL Ratio"

                               @{fg shine}U L   R a t i o@{fg text}


@{b}UL Ratio@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-255@{fg text}
   Input of the upload ratio for the calculation of the UL/DL ratio.

See also @{"¦Cycle Gadget 1" link "E-¦Cycle Gadget 1" 0}
@endnode

@node "E-DL Ratio" "E-DL Ratio"

                               @{fg shine}D L   R a t i o@{fg text}


@{b}DL Ratio@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-255@{fg text}
   Input of the download ratio for the calculation of the UL/DL ratio.

See also @{"¦Cycle Gadget 1" link "E-¦Cycle Gadget 1" 0}
@endnode

@node "E-Total UL`s" "E-Total UL`s"

                             @{fg shine}T o t a l   U L ` s@{fg text}


@{b}Total UL`s@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-65535@{fg text}
   Displays the number of uploaded files.
@endnode

@node "E-Total DL`s" "E-Total DL`s"

                             @{fg shine}T o t a l   D L ` s@{fg text}


@{b}Total DL`s@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-65535@{fg text}
   Displays the number of downloaded files.
@endnode

@node "E-UL Bytes" "E-UL Bytes"

                               @{fg shine}U L   B y t e s@{fg text}


@{b}UL Bytes@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-2147483647@{fg text}
   Displays the size of the uploaded files.
@endnode

@node "E-DL Bytes" "E-DL Bytes"

                               @{fg shine}D L   B y t e s@{fg text}


@{b}DL Bytes@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-2147483647@{fg text}
   Displays the size of the downloaded files.
@endnode

@node "E-Time Limit" "E-Time Limit"

                             @{fg shine}T i m e   L i m i t@{fg text}


@{b}Time Limit@{ub} : @{fg fill}00:00:00-18:12:15@{fg text}
   Input of the maximum online time per day. The exceeding of the time
   will cause an automatic logoff. The user can logon earliest after 12
   hours delay.

See also @{"¦Cycle Gadget 1" link "E-¦Cycle Gadget 1" 0}
@endnode

@node "E-Use" "E-Use"

                                    @{fg shine}U s e@{fg text}


@{b}Use@{ub} : @{fg fill}ON|OFF@{fg text}
   Setting whether Time Limit and Time Used should be used per day or only
   per call.
   @{fg fill}ON@{fg text}  = per day
   @{fg fill}OFF@{fg text} = per call
   e.g. Guest -> In this case Time Limit and Time Used should be used per
                 call otherwise it could happen that the second or third
                 guest user has no online time left and will be kicked
                 out.

See also @{"¦Cycle Gadget 1" link "E-¦Cycle Gadget 1" 0}
@endnode

@node "E-Time Used" "E-Time Used"

                              @{fg shine}T i m e   U s e d@{fg text}


@{b}Time Used@{ub} : @{fg fill}00:00:00-18:12:15@{fg text}
   Displays the time already used on this day.
@endnode

@node "E-Last Onl. Time" "E-Last Onl. Time"

                         @{fg shine}L a s t   O n l .   T i m e@{fg text}


@{b}Last Onl. Time@{ub} : @{fg fill}78-01-01 00:00:00 until 2099-12-31 23:59:59@{fg text}
   Displays date and time of the last call of the user.
@endnode

@node "E-Tot. Onl. Time" "E-Tot. Onl. Time"

                         @{fg shine}T o t .   O n l .   T i m e@{fg text}


@{b}Tot. Onl. Time@{ub} : @{fg fill}00-00-00 00:00:00 until 99-11-29 23:59:59@{fg text}
   Displays the whole online time of all calls of this user.
   This will be calculated as follows:
   YY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS The year will be calculated with 12 (0-11) months and
                     each month with 30 (0-29) days.
@endnode

@node "E-Extra Info TXT" "E-Extra Info TXT"

                         @{fg shine}E x t r a   I n f o   T X T@{fg text}


@{b}Extra Info TXT@{ub} : @{fg fill}1-30 Characters@{fg text}
   Input of a textfile which the user will get displayed at the Logon. The
   file has to be located in the path of the SystemTextLocation.
   e.g. user groups of a computer club

See also @{"¦Cycle Gadget 1" link "E-¦Cycle Gadget 1" 0}
@endnode

@node "E-Logoff Type" "E-Logoff Type"

                            @{fg shine}L o g o f f   T y p e@{fg text}


@{b}Logoff Type@{ub} : @{fg fill}Undefined|Goodbye|Sleep|Overtime|@{fg text}
              @{fg fill}12HrsTry|Carrier|Illegal|Reset@{fg text}
   Displays the way of the last logoff.
   @{fg fill}Goodbye@{fg text}  = standard logoff
   @{fg fill}Sleep@{fg text}    = if there was no keystroke within the last 2 minutes
   @{fg fill}Overtime@{fg text} = maximum online time reached and kicked out
   @{fg fill}12HrsTry@{fg text} = try to logon within 12 hours
   @{fg fill}Carrier@{fg text}  = lost Carrier -> line interrupted or hang-up
   @{fg fill}Illegal@{fg text}  = 3 times input of the wrong password
   @{fg fill}Reset@{fg text}    = kicked out from the SysOp (Reset System)
   NOTE: In case of the logoff type carrier there will automatically
         executed a modem report on the next logon, logoff, upload and
         download to give the user the possibility to find the error if the
         line was noisy. In any case this will contribute to a regular
         logoff in the mailbox.
@endnode

@node "E-Last Onl. Baud" "E-Last Onl. Baud"

                         @{fg shine}L a s t   O n l .   B a u d@{fg text}


@{b}Last Onl. Baud@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-999999@{fg text}
   Displays the connect speed of the last call.
@endnode

@node "E-Total Login" "E-Total Login"

                            @{fg shine}T o t a l   L o g i n@{fg text}


@{b}Total Login@{ub} : @{fg fill}0-65535@{fg text}
   Displays the number of calls of this user.
@endnode

@node "E-Save Setups" "E-Save Setups"

                            @{fg shine}S a v e   S e t u p s@{fg text}


@{b}Save Setups@{ub} : @{fg fill}ON|OFF@{fg text}
   Setting if the personal setups will be saved
   @{fg fill}ON@{fg text}  = all changes will be saved
   @{fg fill}OFF@{fg text} = the changes of the user will not be saved
   e.g. Guest -> the changes must not be saved

See also @{"¦Cycle Gadget 1" link "E-¦Cycle Gadget 1" 0}
@endnode

@node "E-Get Menu CS" "E-Get Menu CS"

                            @{fg shine}G e t   M e n u   C S@{fg text}


@{b}Get Menu CS@{ub} : @{fg fill}ON|OFF@{fg text}
   Setting if the user gets the function Chat SysOp
   @{fg fill}ON@{fg text}  = function Chat SysOp available
   @{fg fill}OFF@{fg text} = function Chat SysOp not available
   e.g. protection against too boring user

See also @{"¦Cycle Gadget 1" link "E-¦Cycle Gadget 1" 0}
@endnode

@node "E-Get Menu JM" "E-Get Menu JM"

                            @{fg shine}G e t   M e n u   J M@{fg text}


@{b}Get Menu JM@{ub} : @{fg fill}ON|OFF@{fg text}
   Setting if the user gets the function Join as a Member
   @{fg fill}ON@{fg text}  = function Join as a Member available
   @{fg fill}OFF@{fg text} = function Join as a Member not available
   e.g. Guest -> so that new user can join

See also @{"¦Cycle Gadget 1" link "E-¦Cycle Gadget 1" 0}
@endnode

@node "E-Get Menu CB" "E-Get Menu CB"

                            @{fg shine}G e t   M e n u   C B@{fg text}


@{b}Get Menu CB@{ub} : @{fg fill}ON|OFF@{fg text}
   Setting if the user gets the function Call Back
   @{fg fill}ON@{fg text}  = function Call Back available
   @{fg fill}OFF@{fg text} = function Call Back not available
   e.g. SysOp -> possibility for a call back. Attention! This will cost
                 your money, so be careful!

See also @{"¦Cycle Gadget 1" link "E-¦Cycle Gadget 1" 0}
@endnode

@node "Distribution" "Distribution"

                           @{fg shine}D I S T R I B U T I O N@{fg text}


@{b}GMC-BBS@{ub} is since the version 2.50 @{b}Freeware@{ub}.

The program may be freely distributed and copied, as long as the following
@{b}conditions are fulfilled@{ub}:

 - The @{b}sales price@{ub} must not be higher than the cost of two (empty) disks
   plus a nominal copying fee plus costs for shipping. The total price must
   not be higher than 100 ATS or the equivalent in any other currency.

 - All parts of the program and the documentation must be @{b}complete@{ub}. The
   distribution of single files or incomplete subsets of the original
   distribution is not allowed.

 - @{b}Program and documentation may not be changed in any way@{ub}. Exception (this
   means: acceptable) is the use of archivers such as `LHA' and packers
   like `Imploder' or `Powerpacker', as long as it remains possible to
   retrieve the original program/data.
@endnode

@node "History" "History"

                                @{fg shine}H I S T O R Y@{fg text}


@{b}Version 2.62 Revision 24-07-1997@{ub}

 - Installer Script written (english and german)

 - Scripts from the ENV: and ENVARC: removed

 - Changes in "bbs.config"

   SystemFileLocation= removed
   SystemProtLocation= removed
   SystemStatLocation= removed
   SystemTextLocation= removed
   SystemUserLocation= removed

   BBS_TextLocation=  added
   CaptureLocation=   added
   Help_TextLocation= added
   ScriptsLocation=   added
   SystemLocation=    added

 - Capture Files renamed

   Capture.File.YY.MM -> BBS_YY.MM
   Chat.File.YY.MM    -> Chat_YY.MM
   Modem.File.YY.MM   -> Modem_YY.MM

@{b}Version 2.61 Revision 10-07-1997@{ub}

 - EEU.PRG Version 1.22 Revision 09-07-1997
   Will work now without NTSC monitor driver.
   "Email Address" instead of "Comment User"

 - Bug corrected in WP if the max. number of users will be reached.

 - Setup Menu
   SS = Show Setup will show the Registration_Number if available
   CC to EC = Edit Computer renamed
   CU to EE = Edit Email Address renamed
   CM to EM = Edit Modem renamed
   CP to EP = Edit Password renamed

@{b}Version 2.60 Revision 07-06-1997@{ub}

 - Function AD = Actual Directory removed (see also CD = Change Directory)
 - Function CP = Change to Previous Directory removed (see also CD)
 - Function CR = Change to Root Directory removed (see also CD)

 - Function CD = Change Directory extended
 - Function CA = Change Area extended

 Syntax: CD Price (changes to Directory Price)
         CD \     (changes to Main Directory)
         CD .     (changes to Main Directory)
         CD ..    (changes to parent Directory 1 step)
         CD ...   (changes to parent Directory 2 steps)
         CD ....  (each dot means one more Directory)
         CD       (displays the current Directory)

         CA       (displays the current Directory)

 - Function RD = Read Doc File renamed to RF = Read File

 - Functions which need files for execution will only be displayed if files
   are really available. The same is valid if Files or Directories are
   required.
   dependence on Files         : DL, PF, RB, RF, RM
   dependence on Dirs or Files : DE, RE, SC
   CA and CD are always available, because this functions are also needed
   for displaying the current directory.

 - English documentation as Amiga Guide and TXT File

@{b}Version 2.50 Revision 14-04-1997@{ub}

 - GMC-BBS changed from Shareware to Freeware

 - Modem report installed
   tested with USRobotics Courier V.Everything and ZyXEL Elite 2864

 - Modem prepared for x2 Connects

 - Separate Security level for Pack Files

 - Execute Script implemented

 - German documentation as Amiga Guide and TXT File

@{b}My plans for the future:@{ub}

 - support of Graphic boards

 - support of OwnDevUnit.library
   which is copyrighted by Christopher A. Wichura.
@endnode

